verbose_text: The interleukin-1 beta (IL-1beta) is a mediator of both bacterial and viral OM and has influence on many different target cells, thus it stimulates proinflammatory network in the middle ear and could induce activation and proliferation of fibroblast and growth of osteoclasts in the middle ear possibly leading to fibrosis and bone erosion [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
evidence: interleukin-1 beta (IL-1beta) is a mediator of both bacterial and viral OM
